        "timestamp": "2018-09-20 08:16:24.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 3: Code-Review-1\n\nFound an integration issue, wherein after executing https based restapi , “PKIX path building failed” and “unable to find valid certification path to requested target” for AAI is coming. Looking into same.\n\nHence this patch and patches related to it can't be merged till above problem is resolved.",
        "patchset_number": 3
      },
      {
        "id": "c5517ee7cde978955170cae04f6a736b84673c37",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 1443,
          "name": "Gaurav Agrawal",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "gaurav.agrawal@huawei.com",
          "username": "agrawalgaurav"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2018-09-20 13:12:07.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 3: -Code-Review\n\nThere are 3 java keystore files in running environment. \n/opt/onap/sdnc/data/stores/truststore.onap.client.jks\n/opt/onap/ccsdk/data/stores/truststore.onap.client.jks\n/opt/onap/sdnc/data/stores/truststore.openecomp.client.jks\n\nThere is no problem if from DG we uses either of the first two keystore files, and I assume that truststore.openecomp.client.jks is already deprecated, if that is a case than I have done basic sanity test of RestapiCallNode for \"http\" as well as \"https\" and it works fine and so I am not expecting any issues because of this commit.",
        "patchset_number": 3
      },
